channel.title: Tech
channel.description: This is a randomly ordered feed of the most recent entries from Tech, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Cluely’s Roy Lee hints that viral hype is not enough
item.description: Lee declined to share Cluely's financial metrics just four months after boasting how quickly the startup is growing.

item.title: Lucid Motors’ chief engineer leaves after 10 years
item.description: Eric Bach, who was once the director of engineering at Tesla, is out amid a larger executive shakeup at the company.

item.title: Lina Khan to co-chair NYC mayor-elect Zohran Mamdani’s transition team
item.description: Khan's appointment sends a message to the tech industry, whose most powerful players have already been critical of Mamdani, a Democratic socialist.

item.title: University of Pennsylvania confirms hacker stole data during cyberattack
item.description: Penn experienced a data breach on Friday as hackers sent messages boasting of the hack to the university community.

item.title: Apple nears deal to pay Google $1B annually to power new Siri, report says
item.description: Apple is turning to Google's technology to help revamp Siri and power a slate of upcoming features for the voice assistant.

item.title: Motion Picture Association hits Meta with cease-and-desist over use of ‘PG-13’ label
item.description: The MPA sent Meta a cease-and-desist over its use of the term 'PG-13' in Instagram teen ratings system.

item.title: Pinterest CEO touts open source AI: ‘tremendous performance’ with reduced costs
item.description: Pinterest CEO Bill Ready says open source AI is offering cost savings to the company, particularly in visual search.

item.title: This startup’s metal stacks could help solve AI’s massive heat problem
item.description: Alloy Enterprises has developed a new additive manufacturing technique that can improve liquid cooling performance while bringing it to new parts of t...

item.title: The Best Travel Totes for Every Kind of Trip (2025)
item.description: These hard-working travel totes handle everything from a work trip to a weekend getaway.

item.title: Google gets the US government’s green light to acquire Wiz for $32B
item.description: Google announced its intent to acquire cloud security company Wiz in March and the deal is now on track to close in early 2026.
